.\" Manpage for flatpak-automatic.
.TH FLATPAK-AUTOMATIC 1 "April 2026" "flatpak-automatic" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
flatpak-automatic \- Enterprise update automation for Flatpak
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B flatpak-automatic
[\fB\-d\fR] [\fB\-t\fR] [\fB\-f\fR] [\fB\-s\fR] [\fB\-l\fR] [\fB\-a\fR] [\fB\-u\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B flatpak-automatic
is a strictly typed, enterprise-grade Python daemon designed to autonomously manage Flatpak updates. It features systemd integration, Snapper filesystem rollback support, and comprehensive alerting via Apprise, Mail, and native Webhooks.

.SH NON-ROOT MODE
To execute the updater without elevated privileges, utilize the user-level systemd units:
.PP
\fBsystemctl --user enable flatpak-automatic-user.timer\fR
.br
\fBsystemctl --user start flatpak-automatic-user.timer\fR
.PP
This isolates update operations within the user session for enhanced security.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-setup
Launch the interactive configuration wizard to generate the sysconfig file.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dry\-run
Simulate the update process without applying changes or triggering snapshots.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-test\-notify
Send a test notification to all configured endpoints.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Force the update process, bypassing the minimum delay guard.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-status
Display a system monitoring overview of configuration and pending updates.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-history
Display recent execution history from journalctl.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-apply\-schedule
Apply systemd timer overrides based on config settings.
.SH FILES
.I /etc/sysconfig/flatpak-automatic
.RS
Primary configuration file.
.RE
.SH AUTHOR
Maintained by the FedoraBee community.
